ce:section.ce:para:
The feasibility of the fluorescence nanoprobe based on TA-Cu NCs for morin detection was investigated by recording the fluorescence emission spectra of 434 nm with different amount of morin (0, 0.05, 0.1, 0.3, 0.5, 0.7, 1, 3, 5, 10, 15, 20, 25, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70, 80, 90, 100, 110, 120, 130, 140 and 150 μM). Fig. 4
                        A showed the fluorescence emission spectra of this fluorescence detection system with increasing amount of morin. As illustrated in Fig. 4A, with the concentration of morin increased, the fluorescence intensity of TA-Cu NCs + morin system decreased at 434 nm. It indicated that the fluorescence of TA-Cu NCs could be quenched by morin. It could be seen from Fig. 4B, there was an excellent linear relationship between the relative fluorescence intensity (F0/F) and the morin concentrations in the range of 0.5–110 μM. The linear fitting equation of the fluorescence detection system was F0/F = 0.0267[Morin]+0.9585, and the corresponding linear correlation coefficient was 0.9949 with detection limit (LOD) of 0.062 μM (S/N = 3). Compared to other detection methods, this proposed method possessed wider linear range and lower LOD (Table 1
                        ). Furthermore, this proposed approach revealed great advantages of low cost, easy operation and simple “turn off” process, and suggested huge potential for rapid determination of morin in bovine serum samples.
